yonder in that mirror.

419
00:30:24,956 --> 00:30:26,874
Do as I say.

420
00:30:39,888 --> 00:30:41,847
Look at yourself.

421
00:30:43,975 --> 00:30:46,727
What do you see, girl?

422
00:30:46,812 --> 00:30:49,021
You see the body of a woman -

423
00:30:49,105 --> 00:30:51,982
the temple of creation and motherhood.

424
00:30:52,067 --> 00:30:55,194
You see the flesh of Eve
that man since Adam has profaned.

425
00:30:56,196 --> 00:30:58,447
That body was meant
for begettin' children.

426
00:30:58,532 --> 00:31:01,242
It was not meant for the lust of men.

427
00:31:03,411 --> 00:31:05,496
Do you want more children, Willa?

428
00:31:05,580 --> 00:31:07,248
I -

429
00:31:07,332 --> 00:31:08,916
No.

430
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,169
It’s the business of this marriage
to mind those two you have now...

431
00:31:12,254 --> 00:31:14,213
not to beget more.

432
00:31:14,297 --> 00:31:15,798
Yes.

433
00:31:23,348 --> 00:31:27,101
All right, you can get in bed now
and stop shiverin'.

434
00:31:29,312 --> 00:31:31,605
Help me to get clean...

435
00:31:31,690 --> 00:31:34,859
so I can be what Ηarry
wants me to be.

436
00:31:41,992 --> 00:31:45,160
Meanest, orneriest, sneakingest critter
in the whole river, boy.

437
00:31:45,245 --> 00:31:47,162
A gar.

438
00:31:48,206 --> 00:31:51,041
- Ηere are your can of hooks, Uncle Birdie.
- Pshaw, boy.

439
00:31:51,126 --> 00:31:54,670
Ain't a hook in the land
strong enough to land Mr. Gar.

440
00:31:54,754 --> 00:31:58,257
What a feller needs is mother wit
and a horsehair.

441
00:31:59,259 --> 00:32:01,635
Golly. Won't it bust it, Uncle Birdie?

442
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:04,889
Nah, a horsehair will hold
a lumpin' whale.

443
00:32:04,973 --> 00:32:07,474
- You mind my cussin', boy?
- No.

444
00:32:07,559 --> 00:32:11,437
Well, the reason I ask,
your step-pa bein' a preacher and all -

445
00:32:14,691 --> 00:32:17,443
Never was much of a one
for preachers my own self.

446
00:32:18,486 --> 00:32:20,487
I don't know what's wrong
up at your house...

447
00:32:20,572 --> 00:32:23,324
but always remember, cap...

448
00:32:23,408 --> 00:32:25,993
if you're ever in trouble,
holler and come a-runnin'.

449
00:32:26,995 --> 00:32:28,996
Uncle Birdie's your friend.

450
00:32:34,002 --> 00:32:38,464
There! There, you slimy, snag-toothed,
bait-stealin' so-and-so!

451
00:32:38,548 --> 00:32:40,799
- [ Congregation ] Amen! Amen!
- Amen!

452
00:32:40,884 --> 00:32:42,384
[ Congregation ]
Amen!

453
00:32:42,469 --> 00:32:44,720
- You have all sinned.
- Yes! Yes!

454
00:32:44,804 --> 00:32:47,973
Which one of you can say,
as I can say...

455
00:32:48,975 --> 00:32:51,644
- that you drove a good man to murder?
- [ Gasping ]

456
00:32:51,728 --> 00:32:55,356
Because I kept a-houndin' him
for perfume...

457
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,608
and clothes and face paint!

458
00:32:57,692 --> 00:33:01,612
- [ Gasping ]
- And he slew two human beings!

459
00:33:01,696 --> 00:33:05,157
- [ Exclaiming ]
- And he come to me, and he said...

460
00:33:05,241 --> 00:33:10,245
"Take this money and buy yourself
the clothes and the paint!"

461
00:33:10,330 --> 00:33:13,040
- [ Congregation ] Yes! Yes!
- But, brethren -

462
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:17,086
