477
00:34:36,124 --> 00:34:39,126
- What are you doing, boy?
- Gettin' Pearl to bed.

478
00:34:39,210 --> 00:34:42,212
- What's taking you so long about it?
- Nothing.

479
00:34:48,303 --> 00:34:50,220
What's that you're playin' with?

480
00:34:50,305 --> 00:34:55,059
Uh, Pearl's junk. Mom gets mad
when she plays out here and don't put it away.

481
00:34:55,143 --> 00:34:57,102
Come on, children.

482
00:34:59,939 --> 00:35:02,608
Off to bed with the both of you.

483
00:35:09,407 --> 00:35:11,325
Come here, John.

484
00:35:14,412 --> 00:35:17,039
Your mother tells me you tattled on me.

485
00:35:17,123 --> 00:35:19,583
She said you told her
I asked where that money was hid.

486
00:35:19,667 --> 00:35:22,044
[ Chuckles ]

487
00:35:22,128 --> 00:35:24,421
That wasn't very nice, boy.

488
00:35:24,506 --> 00:35:26,173
Have a heart.

489
00:35:26,257 --> 00:35:28,467
Yeah.

490
00:35:28,551 --> 00:35:32,262
Well, it doesn't matter.
It’s your word against mine.

491
00:35:32,347 --> 00:35:34,556
It’s me your mother believes.

492
00:35:39,854 --> 00:35:42,815
Were you impudent again
to Mr. Powell, John?

493
00:35:42,899 --> 00:35:44,900
Mom, I didn't mean it.

494
00:35:46,194 --> 00:35:48,821
What were you impudent about?

495
00:35:48,905 --> 00:35:51,240
He asked me about the money again, Mom.

496
00:35:52,242 --> 00:35:54,660
John, you always make up that lie.

497
00:35:54,744 --> 00:35:56,870
There is no money.

498
00:35:56,955 --> 00:35:59,915
Why can't you get that through your head?

499
00:35:59,999 --> 00:36:02,626
The boy's as stubborn
and as mulish as a sheep.

500
00:36:02,710 --> 00:36:04,837
- It’s a shame.
- Good night, Icey.

501
00:36:04,921 --> 00:36:06,755
- Good night, honey.
- Good night, Walt.

502
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,382
Good night, Willa.

503
00:36:10,426 --> 00:36:12,970
Plan on a longer visit next time.

504
00:36:13,054 --> 00:36:15,806
You hardly get settled
before you're frettin' to get home again.

505
00:36:15,890 --> 00:36:18,475
I'm needed to keep peace
and harmony betwixt them.

506
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:21,395
It’s my burden,
and I'm proud of it, Icey.

507
00:36:31,406 --> 00:36:34,992
- Where's the money hid?
- I don't know.

508
00:36:35,076 --> 00:36:37,870
She thinks that money's
at the bottom of the river.

509
00:36:37,954 --> 00:36:40,330
But you and me, we know better,
don't we, little lad?

510
00:36:40,415 --> 00:36:42,875
I don't know nothin'.

511
00:36:42,959 --> 00:36:46,420
Well, never mind, boy.
The summer's young yet.

512
00:36:46,504 --> 00:36:48,505
Pearl?

513
00:36:48,590 --> 00:36:50,257
Come here.

514
00:36:51,384 --> 00:36:53,343
[ Grunts ]

515
00:36:53,428 --> 00:36:56,346
John's a fella likes to keep secrets.
I’ll tell you a secret.

516
00:36:56,431 --> 00:36:58,098
Yes?

517
00:36:58,183 --> 00:37:00,893
I knowed your daddy.

518
00:37:00,977 --> 00:37:03,770
And you know what your daddy told me?

519
00:37:03,855 --> 00:37:05,898
Ηe said,
"You tell my little girl Pearl...

520
00:37:05,982 --> 00:37:08,483
that there's to be no secrets
between her and you."

521
00:37:08,568 --> 00:37:11,570
- Yes?
- All right. Now it's your turn.

522
00:37:12,906 --> 00:37:14,448
What secret shall I tell?

523
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:16,992
Oh, uh, what's your name?

524
00:37:17,076 --> 00:37:18,702
[ Pearl Giggles ]

525
00:37:18,786 --> 00:37:21,496
You're just fooling.
My name's Pearl.

526
00:37:21,581 --> 00:37:25,125
Tsk, tsk, tsk.
Well, I reckon I'll have to try again.

527
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:27,127
Uh, where's the money hid?

528
00:37:27,212 --> 00:37:29,671
[ Gasps ]

529
00:37:30,632 --> 00:37:34,051
Pearl, you swore you wouldn't tell!
You swore! You swore! You swore!

530
00:37:34,135 --> 00:37:37,012
You hit Daddy with a hairbrush.

531
00:37:37,096 --> 00:37:38,889
Oh.

532
00:37:38,973 --> 00:37:42,434
Now, you see? We just can't have
anything to do with John.

533
00:37:42,518 --> 00:37:44,937
You and me are goin' down
to the parlor, Pearl.

534
00:38:01,996 --> 00:38:05,832
[ Powell ] John was just plumb bad
through and through.

535
00:38:05,917 --> 00:38:09,002
- [ Pearl ] John's bad.
- Yes, John's bad.

536
00:38:10,004 --> 00:38:12,589
[ Pearl ]
Tell me another secret about my dad.

537
00:38:12,674 --> 00:38:14,549
[ Powell ]
Oh, no. Your turn.

538
00:38:14,634 --> 00:38:17,928
[ Pearl ]
All right. What secret shall I tell?

539
00:38:18,012 --> 00:38:20,514
Mmm. Where's the money hid?

540
00:38:20,598 --> 00:38:23,558
- John's bad.
- Where's the money hid?

541
00:38:23,643 --> 00:38:27,437
You tell me, you little wretch,
or I’ll tear your arm off!

542
00:38:27,522 --> 00:38:30,065
[ Screaming ]

543
00:38:39,993 --> 00:38:43,453
- Icey, I'm worried about Willa.
- How do you mean?

544
00:38:43,538 --> 00:38:46,164
Well, I'm figurin' how to say it
so as you won't get mad.

545
00:38:46,249 --> 00:38:48,166
Say what, Walt Spoon?

546
00:38:48,251 --> 00:38:50,627
- There's something wrong about it, Mother.
- About what?

547
00:38:50,712 --> 00:38:53,672
- About Mr. Powell, all of it.
- Walt!

548
00:38:53,756 --> 00:38:55,799
Now, Mother, a body's
got a right to their feelings.

549
00:38:55,883 --> 00:38:58,927
May the Lord have mercy on you,
Walt Spoon.

550
00:38:59,012 --> 00:39:00,470
Now, Mother, I was just -

551
00:39:00,555 --> 00:39:03,056
[ Willa Murmuring ]

552
00:39:04,559 --> 00:39:06,476
Amen.

553
00:39:07,895 --> 00:39:10,188
Are you through praying?

554
00:39:10,273 --> 00:39:12,274
I'm through, Ηarry.

555
00:39:12,358 --> 00:39:14,985
You were listening
outside the parlor window.

556
00:39:15,069 --> 00:39:18,655
- It ain't in the river, is it, Harry?
- Answer me.

557
00:39:18,740 --> 00:39:21,575
Ben never told you he throwed it
in the river, did he?

558
00:39:32,587 --> 00:39:34,755
The children know where it's hid.

559
00:39:34,839 --> 00:39:37,341
John knows. Is that it, Harry?

560
00:39:42,430 --> 00:39:45,682
Then it's still here amongst us...

561
00:39:45,767 --> 00:39:47,684
tainting us.

562
00:39:50,813 --> 00:39:54,107
You must have known about it
all along, Harry.

563
00:39:54,192 --> 00:39:57,903
But that ain't the reason
why you married me.

564
00:39:57,987 --> 00:39:59,946
I know that much.

565
00:40:01,532 --> 00:40:04,117
Because the Lord just wouldn't let it be.

566
00:40:05,119 --> 00:40:08,372
He made you marry me...

567
00:40:08,456 --> 00:40:11,458
so you could show me
the way and the Iife...

568
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:15,629
and the salvation of my soul.

569
00:40:16,631 --> 00:40:18,924
Ain't that so, Harry?

570
00:40:19,926 --> 00:40:23,720
So you might say that it was the money
that brung us together.

571
00:40:24,806 --> 00:40:27,474
The rest of it don't matter.

572
00:40:38,111 --> 00:40:42,114
[ Starter Cranking, Engine Sputtering ]

573
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:47,744
[ Starter Cranking ]

574
00:40:54,168 --> 00:40:56,878
[ Engine Sputtering ]

575
00:41:01,467 --> 00:41:03,635
[ Engine Running ]

576
00:41:24,991 --> 00:41:26,616
Walt! Come quick!

577
00:41:26,701 --> 00:41:29,411
- What's wrong, Mother?
- Shh! He's in there.

578
00:41:29,495 --> 00:41:30,954
- Who?
- Mr. Powell.

579
00:41:31,038 --> 00:41:34,124
Willa has run away.

580
00:41:34,208 --> 00:41:35,876
I'll be switched. Just went?

581
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,462
She took out some time in the night
in that old Model "T."

582
00:41:38,546 --> 00:41:41,006
- Oh, is he hit pretty bad?
- All to pieces.

583
00:41:41,090 --> 00:41:43,216
- There's a little peach brandy in here.
- Walt!

584
00:41:43,301 --> 00:41:46,136
- A man of the cloth?
- Well, just a sip.

585
00:41:47,138 --> 00:41:50,098
- Walt Spoon, that's for sickness in the house!
- [ Coughs ]

586
00:41:51,392 --> 00:41:54,811
- Well, what can we do, Mother?
- I thought if you went and talked to him -
you know, another man.

587
00:41:54,896 --> 00:41:57,564
- Oh, no, now, Mother, please.
No, I'm no good at -
- Get in there.

588
00:41:57,648 --> 00:42:00,484
[ Sobbing ]

589
00:42:00,568 --> 00:42:03,236
- Mr. Powell?
- A strange woman is a narrow pit.

590
00:42:03,321 --> 00:42:04,488
[ Icey ]
Amen. Amen.

591
00:42:04,572 --> 00:42:08,408
She lieth in wait as for prey
and increaseth the transgressors among men.

592
00:42:09,911 --> 00:42:12,871
Oh, my dear, dear friends,
whatever would I do without you?

593
00:42:12,955 --> 00:42:14,456
Mr. Powell!

594
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:16,500
Well, if there's anything -
anything we can -

595
00:42:16,584 --> 00:42:19,878
No, it's my shame. It’s my crown of thorns.
I must wear it bravely.

596
00:42:19,962 --> 00:42:21,922
What could have possessed that girl?

597
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:23,507
- Satan.
- Ah!

598
00:42:23,591 --> 00:42:25,175
Didn't you have no inklin'?

599
00:42:25,259 --> 00:42:28,637
Yes, I did from the very first night.

600
00:42:28,721 --> 00:42:31,431
- First night?
- Our honeymoon.

601
00:42:31,516 --> 00:42:33,683
How's that?

602
00:42:33,768 --> 00:42:36,186
She turned me out of the bed.

603
00:42:36,270 --> 00:42:38,772
No.

604
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:41,650
- WeIl, what do you figure to do?
- Do?

605
00:42:41,734 --> 00:42:44,903
Why, just stay right here
and take care of them kids.

606
00:42:44,987 --> 00:42:48,198
Maybe it was never meant for a woman
like Willa to taint their young lives.

607
00:42:48,282 --> 00:42:51,576
- Mmm. Mmm.
- It’s mighty brave of you, Preacher.

608
00:42:51,661 --> 00:42:55,705
Oh, I reckon it was just ordained
that way, brother Spoon.

609
00:42:55,790 --> 00:42:58,375
Didn't - Didn't she leave no word?

610
00:42:59,460 --> 00:43:03,129
A scrawl on a notepaper on the bureau.

611
00:43:03,214 --> 00:43:05,549
I burned it.

612
00:43:05,633 --> 00:43:08,927
Tore it up and burned it.
It stank so strong of hellfire.

613
00:43:09,011 --> 00:43:10,804
Amen.

614
00:43:10,888 --> 00:43:14,057
The pitcher has went to the well
once too often, friends.

615
00:43:14,141 --> 00:43:16,893
Oh, she’ll come draggin' her tail back home.

616
00:43:16,978 --> 00:43:20,897
She'll not be back.
I reckon I'm safe in promisin' you that.

617
00:43:20,982 --> 00:43:23,066
- Maybe she's just run off on a spree.
- No, no.

618
00:43:23,150 --> 00:43:26,361
- Well, there's no harm in hopin'.
- Ain't no sense in it neither.

619
00:43:27,488 --> 00:43:30,782
I figured somethin' like that was brewin'
when she went to bed last night.

620
00:43:30,866 --> 00:43:32,200
How?

621
00:43:33,661 --> 00:43:36,246
Well, she tarried around in the kitchen
after I'd gone up...

622
00:43:36,330 --> 00:43:38,582
and when I went downstairs
to see what was wrong -

623
00:43:38,666 --> 00:43:40,917
What?

624
00:43:41,002 --> 00:43:43,753
Well, she'd found this jar
of dandelion wine...

625
00:43:43,838 --> 00:43:47,340
that the husband - this Harper -
had hid somewheres in the cellar.

626
00:43:48,843 --> 00:43:52,053
- She was drinkin'.
- Oh!

627
00:43:52,138 --> 00:43:53,847
I tried to save her.

628
00:43:53,931 --> 00:43:57,517
I know you did, Mr. Powell.
I know how hard you tried.

629
00:43:57,602 --> 00:44:00,520
But the devil wins sometimes.

630
00:44:00,605 --> 00:44:03,857
Can't nobody say
I didn't do my best to save her.

631
00:45:03,084 --> 00:45:05,418
[ Powell ]
♪ Leaning ♪

632
00:45:05,503 --> 00:45:08,046
♪ Leaning ♪

633
00:45:08,130 --> 00:45:13,343
♪ Safe and secure from all alarms ♪

634
00:45:13,427 --> 00:45:18,682
♪ Leaning ♪

635
00:45:18,766 --> 00:45:24,104
♪ Leaning on the everlasting arms ♪♪

636
00:45:26,107 --> 00:45:28,024
Children!

637
00:45:29,151 --> 00:45:31,111
[ Singsongy ]
Children.

638
00:45:40,287 --> 00:45:42,205
Children.

639
00:45:42,289 --> 00:45:44,999
- [ Footsteps Departing ]
- Pearl?

640
00:45:48,129 --> 00:45:51,047
Careful. Here.

641
00:45:51,132 --> 00:45:53,425
Why do we have to hide, John?

642
00:45:53,509 --> 00:45:55,468
[ Powell ]
Children.

643
00:45:56,512 --> 00:45:59,013
- Where's Mom?
- She's gone to Moundsville.

644
00:45:59,098 --> 00:46:02,559
- To see Dad?
- Yes, I reckon that's it.

645
00:46:02,643 --> 00:46:04,144
[ Door Closes ]

646
00:46:10,317 --> 00:46:13,153
Now, listen to me, Pearl.
You and me is runnin' off tonight.

647
00:46:13,237 --> 00:46:14,571
- Why?
- [ Powell ] Children.

648
00:46:14,655 --> 00:46:18,074
If we stay here,
something awful will happen to us.

649
00:46:18,159 --> 00:46:21,411
- Won't Daddy Powell take care of us?
- No.

650
00:46:21,495 --> 00:46:24,289
- That's just it. No.
- [ Footsteps ]

651
00:46:31,672 --> 00:46:34,507
- Where are we going, John?
- Somewheres. I don't know yet.

652
00:46:34,592 --> 00:46:35,884
[ Jars Rattle ]

653
00:46:35,968 --> 00:46:37,552
I'm hungry, John.

654
00:46:37,636 --> 00:46:40,680
- We'll steal somethin' to eat.
- It'll spoil our suppers.

655
00:46:40,765 --> 00:46:42,265
[ Powell, Singsongy ]
Pearl.

656
00:46:47,104 --> 00:46:50,106
I can hear you whisperin', children,
so I know you're down there.

657
00:46:50,191 --> 00:46:52,901
I can feel myself gettin' awful mad.

658
00:46:56,781 --> 00:46:59,073
I'm out of patience, children.

659
00:46:59,158 --> 00:47:00,950
I'm coming to find you now.

660
00:47:01,035 --> 00:47:02,535
[ Icey ]
Yoo-hoo!

661
00:47:02,620 --> 00:47:05,288
Mr. Powell.

662
00:47:08,834 --> 00:47:11,795
Well, well, Mrs. Spoon.

663
00:47:11,879 --> 00:47:13,630
[ Icey ]
Where are the children?

664
00:47:13,714 --> 00:47:15,882
They're down there in that cellar
playin' games...

665
00:47:15,966 --> 00:47:18,092
and they won't mind me when I call them.

666
00:47:18,177 --> 00:47:20,053
I'm at my wit's end, Mrs. Spoon.

667
00:47:20,137 --> 00:47:23,723
[ Icey ]
Oh. Tsk, tsk. John? Pearl?

668
00:47:23,808 --> 00:47:25,517
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

669
00:47:25,601 --> 00:47:27,435
John! Pearl!

670
00:47:30,523 --> 00:47:32,565
Shake a leg.

671
00:47:38,155 --> 00:47:41,157
[ Powell ]
WelI, well, weIl. What's that?

672
00:47:41,242 --> 00:47:44,536
[ Icey ] Just a little hot supper
I fixed for you and the children.

673
00:47:44,620 --> 00:47:47,247
It seemed the Ieast we could do.

674
00:47:48,582 --> 00:47:51,376
I won't have you worrying
poor Mr. Powell another minute.

675
00:47:51,460 --> 00:47:54,629
Just look at you -
dust and filth from top to toe.

676
00:47:54,713 --> 00:47:57,340
Want me to take 'em up
and wash 'em good?

677
00:47:57,424 --> 00:47:59,968
No. No, thank you, dear Icey.
Thank you.

678
00:48:00,052 --> 00:48:02,011
I'll tend to them. Thank you.

679
00:48:02,096 --> 00:48:04,013
Don't be too hard on 'em, Preacher.

680
00:48:04,098 --> 00:48:06,349
Poor motherless children.

681
00:48:06,433 --> 00:48:10,603
Remember now, Mr. Powell,
don't be afraid to call on us.

682
00:48:15,234 --> 00:48:16,985
Good-bye.

683
00:48:17,069 --> 00:48:20,113
Good-bye, Miz Spoon,
and thanks again.

684
00:48:20,197 --> 00:48:22,031
[ Simpers ]

685
00:48:27,955 --> 00:48:31,875
Now, weren't you afraid, little lambs,
down there in all that dark?

686
00:48:31,959 --> 00:48:34,294
[ Ship Horn Blows ]

687
00:48:41,010 --> 00:48:44,304
[ Crickets Chirping ]

688
00:48:48,392 --> 00:48:51,060
They'll think it was me.

689
00:48:51,145 --> 00:48:54,105
They'll say it was poor old Uncle Birdie.

690
00:48:57,067 --> 00:48:59,819
Aw, if you could've seen it, Bess.

691
00:49:00,988 --> 00:49:03,281
Down there in the deep place...

692
00:49:04,199 --> 00:49:08,036
with her hair wavin' soft and lazy, like...

693
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:10,538
meadow grass under floodwater.

694
00:49:11,665 --> 00:49:14,083
And that slit in her throat...

695
00:49:14,168 --> 00:49:16,461
like she had an extra mouth.

696
00:49:20,841 --> 00:49:24,761
You're the only human mortal
I can go to, Bess.

697
00:49:25,679 --> 00:49:28,598
If I go to the law...

698
00:49:28,682 --> 00:49:30,642
they'll hang it on me.

699
00:49:36,357 --> 00:49:39,901
Sweet heaven, save poor old Uncle Birdie.

700
00:49:45,699 --> 00:49:48,409
- I'm hungry.
- Sure.

701
00:49:48,494 --> 00:49:53,665
And there's fried chicken, sweet potatoes,
corn bread and apple cobbler.

702
00:49:54,625 --> 00:49:57,710
- Can I have my supper, please?
- Naturally.

703
00:49:57,795 --> 00:50:00,463
- Can I have milk too?
- Mm-hmm.

704
00:50:00,547 --> 00:50:03,675
But first, we'll have a little talk -
about our secrets.

705
00:50:03,759 --> 00:50:06,177
- No.
- And why not, pray tell?

706
00:50:06,261 --> 00:50:07,595
'Cause John said I mustn't.

707
00:50:07,680 --> 00:50:10,556
- [ Table Rattles ]
- Never mind what John said!

708
00:50:10,641 --> 00:50:12,684
- John's a meddler.
- [ Pearl Crying ]

709
00:50:12,768 --> 00:50:14,936
Now stop that sniveling.

710
00:50:15,020 --> 00:50:17,480
Look a-here.
You know what that is?

711
00:50:18,232 --> 00:50:20,191
Wanna see something cute?

712
00:50:20,275 --> 00:50:22,735
- Now looky.
- [ Switchblade Snaps Open ]

713
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:25,571
How about that?

714
00:50:25,656 --> 00:50:28,408
This is what I use on meddlers.

715
00:50:28,492 --> 00:50:30,576
John might be a meddler.

716
00:50:30,661 --> 00:50:32,036
Eh-eh! No, no.

717
00:50:32,121 --> 00:50:33,997
No, no, little lamb. Don't touch it.

718
00:50:34,081 --> 00:50:36,207
Don't touch my knife.
That makes me mad.

719
00:50:36,291 --> 00:50:39,252
