- Dead?

970
01:13:24,200 --> 01:13:26,159
Where are you from?

971
01:13:26,243 --> 01:13:28,453
Upriver.

972
01:13:28,537 --> 01:13:33,917
Well, I didn't figure you'd rowed that skiff
all the way up from Parkersburg.

973
01:13:47,848 --> 01:13:50,308
Tell me that story again.

974
01:13:50,393 --> 01:13:52,936
Story? What story, honey?

975
01:13:53,729 --> 01:13:55,271
About them kings...

976
01:13:55,356 --> 01:13:59,359
and the queen found down on the sandbar
that time on the skiff.

977
01:13:59,443 --> 01:14:02,529
Kings? Why, there was only one king, honey.

978
01:14:03,823 --> 01:14:05,782
I mind you said there was two.

979
01:14:07,076 --> 01:14:10,036
Well, shoot now.
Maybe there was.

980
01:14:11,288 --> 01:14:13,706
Yes, come to think of it,
there was two.

981
01:14:23,342 --> 01:14:26,344
- ♪♪ [ Jukebox: Big Band, Slow Tempo ]
- [ People Chattering ]

982
01:14:40,359 --> 01:14:43,027
Must be Thursday.
Here comes Ruby.

983
01:14:50,327 --> 01:14:52,036
Here I go.

984
01:14:58,586 --> 01:15:00,962
Why, you're Ruby.
Ain't you, my child?

985
01:15:01,046 --> 01:15:03,173
- Can I have this?
- Surely.

986
01:15:03,257 --> 01:15:04,966
I'd like to talk to you, my dear.

987
01:15:05,050 --> 01:15:06,968
- Will you buy me an ice cream?
- Of course.

988
01:15:07,052 --> 01:15:09,304
- Watch out, Preacher.
- [ Kid ] Why, Preacher.

989
01:15:09,388 --> 01:15:11,347
Shut your dirty mouths.

990
01:15:16,145 --> 01:15:18,438
♪♪ [ Continues ]

991
01:15:22,735 --> 01:15:24,194
Ain't I pretty?

992
01:15:24,278 --> 01:15:26,946
Why, you're the prettiest thing
I ever seen in all my wanderin'.

993
01:15:28,407 --> 01:15:31,159
Ain't nobody never toId you that, Ruby?

994
01:15:31,243 --> 01:15:32,869
No. No one never did.

995
01:15:33,829 --> 01:15:36,498
There's, uh, two new ones
out your place, ain't there?

996
01:15:36,582 --> 01:15:38,958
Uh-huh.

997
01:15:39,043 --> 01:15:41,294
- What's their names?
- Pearl and John.

998
01:15:41,378 --> 01:15:44,672
Ah, yeah. Is there a doll?

999
01:15:44,757 --> 01:15:46,883
Only they don't never
let me play with it.

1000
01:15:46,967 --> 01:15:48,134
Ah!

1001
01:15:54,808 --> 01:15:57,560
Did you ever see such pretty eyes
in all your born days?

1002
01:15:57,645 --> 01:16:00,021
- [ Cloth Rips ]
- Don't let him get away, sugar.

1003
01:16:00,105 --> 01:16:04,275
He ain't like you all. Next time, I won't
even ask him to buy me an ice cream.

1004
01:16:05,569 --> 01:16:06,736
[ Sighs ]

1005
01:16:13,244 --> 01:16:15,161
I've been bad.

1006
01:16:19,124 --> 01:16:21,209
Ruby, you didn't have money
to buy this.

1007
01:16:21,293 --> 01:16:24,128
- You'll whip me.
- When did I ever?

1008
01:16:24,213 --> 01:16:27,006
- This man at the drugstore, he gave me -
- The drugstore?

1009
01:16:28,717 --> 01:16:32,428
Miz Cooper, I never been
to sewin' lessons all them times.

1010
01:16:32,513 --> 01:16:34,347
What you been up to, Ruby?

1011
01:16:34,431 --> 01:16:36,766
[ Crying ]
I been out with men.

1012
01:16:38,477 --> 01:16:40,395
Child.

1013
01:16:40,479 --> 01:16:42,522
Oh, my God.

1014
01:16:44,900 --> 01:16:48,903
You were lookin' for love, Ruby,
in the only foolish way you knew how.

1015
01:16:53,409 --> 01:16:56,077
We all need love, Ruby.

1016
01:16:56,161 --> 01:16:58,454
I lost the love of my son.

1017
01:16:58,539 --> 01:17:00,707
I found it with you all.

1018
01:17:02,585 --> 01:17:05,920
You're gonna grow up
to be a strong, fine woman...

1019
01:17:06,005 --> 01:17:08,047
and I'm gonna see to it that you do.

1020
01:17:08,132 --> 01:17:09,924
This gentleman weren't like them.

1021
01:17:10,009 --> 01:17:12,760
Ηe just give me a book
and buy me an ice cream.

1022
01:17:12,845 --> 01:17:16,097
- Now, who was this?
- Ηe didn't ask me for nothin'.

1023
01:17:16,181 --> 01:17:17,849
What'd you talk about?

1024
01:17:17,933 --> 01:17:19,976
Pearl and John.

1025
01:17:20,060 --> 01:17:22,020
John and Pearl?

1026
01:17:22,104 --> 01:17:24,272
- Is he their pap?
- I don't know.

1027
01:17:26,108 --> 01:17:28,192
Wonder why he hasn't
been to the house.

1028
01:17:30,237 --> 01:17:32,238
[ Horse Whinnies ]

1029
01:17:36,076 --> 01:17:38,119
[ Chickens Clucking ]

1030
01:17:42,499 --> 01:17:44,667
[ Horse Whinnies ]

1031
01:17:46,545 --> 01:17:49,255
Oh, Miz Cooper! Miz Cooper!

1032
01:17:49,340 --> 01:17:51,799
- What?
- The man! The man!

1033
01:17:56,430 --> 01:17:58,222
Good mornin', ladies.

1034
01:17:58,307 --> 01:17:59,641
How do?

1035
01:17:59,725 --> 01:18:02,352
Why, you're Miz Cooper, I take it.

1036
01:18:02,436 --> 01:18:04,646
It’s about that John and that Pearl?

1037
01:18:04,730 --> 01:18:06,814
Oh, them poor little lambs.

1038
01:18:06,899 --> 01:18:09,317
To think I never hoped
to see them again in this world.

1039
01:18:09,401 --> 01:18:13,821
Oh, dear madam, if you was to know
what a crown of thorns I've borne...

1040
01:18:13,906 --> 01:18:17,116
in my search for them stray chicks.
[ Gasps ]

1041
01:18:17,201 --> 01:18:19,494
Ruby, go fetch them kids.

1042
01:18:19,578 --> 01:18:20,912
[ Sniffles ]

1043
01:18:22,414 --> 01:18:25,708
Oh, madam,
I see you're lookin' at my hands.

1044
01:18:25,793 --> 01:18:28,795
Would you like me to tell you
the little story of left hand and right hand -

1045
01:18:28,879 --> 01:18:30,338
the tale of good and evil?

1046
01:18:30,422 --> 01:18:34,300
It was with this left hand that old brother Cain
struck the blow that laid his brother low -

1047
01:18:34,385 --> 01:18:36,010
Them kids is yours?

1048
01:18:36,095 --> 01:18:38,388
My own flesh and blood.

1049
01:18:38,472 --> 01:18:39,889
Where's your missus?

1050
01:18:39,973 --> 01:18:44,602
Uh, she run off with a drummer -
during prayer meetin'.

1051
01:18:44,687 --> 01:18:46,896
- Where's she at?
- Down the river somewheres.

1052
01:18:46,980 --> 01:18:50,525
Parkersburg maybe or Cincinnati -
one of them Sodoms on the Ohio River.

1053
01:18:50,609 --> 01:18:52,360
She took them kids with her?

1054
01:18:52,444 --> 01:18:55,363
Oh, heaven only knows
what unholy sights and sounds...

1055
01:18:55,447 --> 01:18:59,951
