- ♪ Leaning on Jesus ♪
- ♪ Leaning ♪

1093
01:21:51,081 --> 01:21:53,666
♪ Leaning on ♪

1094
01:21:53,750 --> 01:21:59,630
♪ The everlasting arms ♪♪

1095
01:22:01,049 --> 01:22:02,758
[ Ηushed ]
Shame on you, Ruby...

1096
01:22:02,843 --> 01:22:05,678
mooning around the house
after that mad dog of a man.

1097
01:22:07,264 --> 01:22:09,348
Merciful heavens!

1098
01:22:10,309 --> 01:22:13,477
Ruby, go get the children out of bed
and bring them down here.

1099
01:22:14,646 --> 01:22:16,105
[ Footsteps Climbing Stairs ]

1100
01:22:16,189 --> 01:22:19,692
- Women are such durn fools.
- [ Owl Hoots ]

1101
01:22:34,333 --> 01:22:37,501
[ Rabbit Squealing ]

1102
01:22:37,586 --> 01:22:40,254
It’s a hard world for little things.

1103
01:22:41,757 --> 01:22:45,051
[ Footsteps Pacing ]

1104
01:23:01,526 --> 01:23:05,529
Now, there was this sneakin',
no-account, ornery King Ηerod.

1105
01:23:05,614 --> 01:23:07,865
And when he heard tell
of little Jesus growin' up...

1106
01:23:07,950 --> 01:23:11,619
he figured, "Well, shoot, there won't
be no room for the both of us.

1107
01:23:11,703 --> 01:23:13,621
I'll just nip this in the bud."

1108
01:23:13,705 --> 01:23:17,166
But he wasn't sure which of all them
babies in the land was King Jesus.

1109
01:23:17,250 --> 01:23:21,754
So that cruel old King Ηerod figured
if he was to kill all the babies in the land...

1110
01:23:21,838 --> 01:23:23,506
he'd be sure and get little Jesus.

1111
01:23:24,299 --> 01:23:26,676
And when little King Jesus' ma and pa
heard about this plan...

1112
01:23:26,760 --> 01:23:28,302
what do you reckon
they went and done?

1113
01:23:28,387 --> 01:23:30,680
- They hid in a broom closet.
- They hid under the porch.

1114
01:23:30,764 --> 01:23:33,683
No. They went a-runnin'.

1115
01:23:33,767 --> 01:23:37,478
Well, now, John, you're right.
That's just what they done.

1116
01:23:37,562 --> 01:23:40,147
And little King Jesus' ma and pa
saddled a mule...

1117
01:23:40,232 --> 01:23:42,775
and they rode all the way down
into Egypt land.

1118
01:23:42,859 --> 01:23:46,195
Yeah. And that's where the queen
found 'im in the "billy rushes."

1119
01:23:46,279 --> 01:23:49,323
Oh, no. That wasn't the same story at all.
That was little King Moses.

1120
01:23:49,408 --> 01:23:53,327
But just the same, it did seem
like it was a plague time for little ones...

1121
01:23:53,412 --> 01:23:56,247
them olden days, them hard, hard times.

1122
01:23:56,331 --> 01:23:59,041
[ Clock Strikes 3:00 ]

1123
01:24:03,296 --> 01:24:05,297
[ Powell ]
Figured I was gone, huh?

1124
01:24:05,382 --> 01:24:08,426
Run! Hide in the staircase!
Run quick!

1125
01:24:08,510 --> 01:24:10,011
Ruby! Git!

1126
01:24:10,971 --> 01:24:13,806
- What do you want?
- I want them kids.

1127
01:24:13,890 --> 01:24:17,184
- What do you want them for?
- That's none of your business, madam.

1128
01:24:17,269 --> 01:24:18,978
I'm giving you to the count of three
to get out of here.

1129
01:24:19,062 --> 01:24:21,814
- Then I'm comin' across the kitchen shooting.
- [ Cat Screeches ]

1130
01:24:22,691 --> 01:24:25,234
[ Powell Yelping, Shrieking ]

1131
01:24:25,318 --> 01:24:27,903
[ Squealing, Yelping ]

1132
01:24:31,033 --> 01:24:33,617
- [ Squealing, Yelping Continue ]
- [ Phone Bell Ringing ]

1133
01:24:36,246 --> 01:24:38,372
Miz Booher? Rachel Cooper.

1134
01:24:38,457 --> 01:24:40,583
Get your state troopers out to my place.

1135
01:24:40,667 --> 01:24:42,793
I got somethin' trapped in my barn.

1136
01:24:52,471 --> 01:24:55,389
[ Yawns ]
I'll go see to Pearl.

1137
01:24:55,474 --> 01:24:57,224
I'll make coffee.

1138
01:25:06,610 --> 01:25:08,319
She's all right.

1139
01:25:10,489 --> 01:25:12,239
John, you know, when you're little...

1140
01:25:12,324 --> 01:25:15,659
you have more endurance
than God is ever to grant you again?

1141
01:25:15,744 --> 01:25:19,038
Children are man at his strongest.
They abide.

1142
01:25:19,122 --> 01:25:21,832
[ Sirens Approaching ]

1143
01:25:26,671 --> 01:25:29,173
[ Sirens Wailing ]

1144
01:25:33,345 --> 01:25:34,762
Why didn't you call us before now?

1145
01:25:34,846 --> 01:25:37,389
Didn't want your dirty shoes
trackin' up my clean floors.

1146
01:25:37,474 --> 01:25:39,308
- Is that him, ma'am?
- Yes.

1147
01:25:39,392 --> 01:25:41,435
Mind where you shoot, boys.
There are children here.

1148
01:25:41,520 --> 01:25:45,189
[ Officer ] Ηarry Powell, you're under arrest
for the murder of Willa Ηarper.

1149
01:25:47,317 --> 01:25:48,692
Drop that knife, Powell.

1150
01:25:51,154 --> 01:25:52,071
Don't.

1151
01:25:52,989 --> 01:25:56,408
Don't!

1152
01:25:56,493 --> 01:25:57,618
[ Crying ]

1153
01:25:57,702 --> 01:26:00,788
- Here! Here!
- John! John!

1154
01:26:00,872 --> 01:26:03,749
Take it back, Dad! Take it back!
I don't want it, Dad!

1155
01:26:03,834 --> 01:26:06,043
It’s too much! Ηere!

1156
01:26:06,128 --> 01:26:07,253
Here!

1157
01:26:15,470 --> 01:26:16,804
[ Spectators Muttering ]

1158
01:26:16,888 --> 01:26:19,557
Lynch him! Lynch him!

1159
01:26:19,641 --> 01:26:21,433
Bluebeard!

1160
01:26:21,518 --> 01:26:24,436
- Twenty-five wives!
- And he killed every last one of 'em!

1161
01:26:24,521 --> 01:26:27,565
- The people of Marshall County -
- Bluebeard!

1162
01:26:27,649 --> 01:26:31,694
- [ Spectators Clamoring ]
- Lynch him! Lynch him!

1163
01:26:31,778 --> 01:26:33,195
[ Gavel Rapping ]

1164
01:26:33,280 --> 01:26:36,866
- [ Rapping Continues ]
- [ Man ] Will you identify the prisoner?

1165
01:26:36,950 --> 01:26:38,450
Please, little lad.

1166
01:26:38,535 --> 01:26:40,744
Won't you look yonder
and tell the court...

1167
01:26:40,829 --> 01:26:43,330
if that is the man
that killed your mother?

1168
01:26:43,415 --> 01:26:45,916
[ Spectators Murmuring ]

1169
01:26:50,922 --> 01:26:53,591
It’s all right, Mrs. Cooper.
You can take the little fellow away.

1170
01:26:54,593 --> 01:26:56,927
Merry Christmas to you and yours,
Mrs. Cooper.

1171
01:26:57,012 --> 01:27:00,264
And what's Santa Claus going
to bring you for Christmas, little man?

1172
01:27:00,348 --> 01:27:01,348
Oh-ho.

1173
01:27:01,433 --> 01:27:03,934
[ Spectators Shouting ]
Bluebeard! Bluebeard! Bluebeard!

1174
01:27:04,019 --> 01:27:06,187
[ Spectators Clamoring ]

1175
01:27:07,147 --> 01:27:11,108
- [ Crowd Clamoring In Distance ]
- [ Man ] Bring out that bluebeard!

1176
01:27:11,193 --> 01:27:13,068
[ Icey Screams ]
There's Pearl!

1177
01:27:13,153 --> 01:27:14,862
Get your coats.

1178
01:27:14,946 --> 01:27:16,530
Them's her orphans!

1179
01:27:16,615 --> 01:27:18,741
- Where's Ruby?
- She went.

1180
01:27:18,825 --> 01:27:21,702
Them poor little lambs!

1181
01:27:21,786 --> 01:27:25,956
Them is the ones
he sinned against, my friends!

1182
01:27:26,041 --> 01:27:27,082
[ Cashier ]
Go out the back door.

1183
01:27:27,167 --> 01:27:30,002
[ Walt ] Don't just stand around. Come on.
They're bringing him out.

1184
01:27:31,963 --> 01:27:34,215
[ Clary ]
Ain't we goin' to the bus depot?

1185
01:27:35,926 --> 01:27:39,386
[ Icey ] Draggin' the name of the Lord
through the evil mud of his soul!

1186
01:27:39,471 --> 01:27:41,138
String that bluebeard
up to a pole!

1187
01:27:41,223 --> 01:27:43,724
He's Satan hidin' behind the cross!

1188
01:27:43,808 --> 01:27:46,310
- Come on!
- [ Crowd Clamoring ]

1189
01:28:17,259 --> 01:28:19,760
[ Clamoring ]

1190
01:28:30,689 --> 01:28:32,189
I love him.

1191
01:28:32,274 --> 01:28:34,316
You think he's like them others.

1192
01:28:37,487 --> 01:28:40,114
[ Crowd Clamoring In Distance ]

1193
01:28:40,198 --> 01:28:42,032
You were so mad, you shot him.

1194
01:28:46,413 --> 01:28:48,914
[ Clamoring Continues ]

1195
01:28:58,466 --> 01:28:59,967
- Ηey, Bart.
- Yeah?

1196
01:29:00,051 --> 01:29:01,885
We're savin' this bird up for you.

1197
01:29:01,970 --> 01:29:03,887
This time, it'll be a privilege.

1198
01:29:28,955 --> 01:29:30,998
I'm glad they didn't send me nothin'.

1199
01:29:31,082 --> 01:29:32,708
Whenever they do, it's nothin' I want...

1200
01:29:32,792 --> 01:29:36,295
but just something to show me how fancy
and smart they come up in the world.

1201
01:29:39,257 --> 01:29:42,426
Brrr! Brrr! Mmm!

1202
01:29:42,510 --> 01:29:45,095
Can we give you
your Christmas presents now?

1203
01:29:45,180 --> 01:29:47,931
Shoot. You don't mean to say
you got me a present?

1204
01:29:48,016 --> 01:29:50,059
- [ Mary Giggling ]
- Shoot now.

1205
01:29:56,316 --> 01:29:57,816
Ruby.

1206
01:29:57,901 --> 01:30:00,527
A potholder.

1207
01:30:00,612 --> 01:30:04,198
And it's much neater
than last year, Ruby.

1208
01:30:04,282 --> 01:30:05,783
Clary.

1209
01:30:07,285 --> 01:30:10,704
Another potholder.
Now, ain't that thoughtful?

1210
01:30:10,789 --> 01:30:12,915
I'm always burnin' my hands.

1211
01:30:15,126 --> 01:30:16,627
Oh, this doesn't look basted.

1212
01:30:16,711 --> 01:30:18,212
- This looks made.
- [ Girl Giggles ]

1213
01:30:18,296 --> 01:30:21,465
Oh, and you finished the edge
with a chain stitch.

1214
01:30:21,549 --> 01:30:25,636
- Oh, that's just dandy, Clary.
- [ Girl Laughing ]

1215
01:30:26,513 --> 01:30:30,307
- Another potholder?
- [ Girls Giggling ]

1216
01:30:33,812 --> 01:30:36,688
Oh, now, did you two
make this together?

1217
01:30:36,773 --> 01:30:38,273
You helped us some.

1218
01:30:47,492 --> 01:30:51,537
That's the richest gift
a body could have.

1219
01:30:51,621 --> 01:30:55,249
And your presents are in the cupboard
under the china closet.

1220
01:30:55,333 --> 01:30:57,960
- [ Children Exclaiming ]
- Ruby.

1221
01:31:00,547 --> 01:31:02,506
This is yours.

1222
01:31:04,509 --> 01:31:07,094
[ Children Chattering ]

1223
01:31:07,178 --> 01:31:08,679
[ Gasps ]

1224
01:31:15,854 --> 01:31:18,313
[ Girl ]
Oh, look what you've got!

1225
01:31:18,398 --> 01:31:21,150
Lord save little children.

1226
01:31:21,234 --> 01:31:24,945
You'd think the world would be ashamed to
name such a day as Christmas for one of them...

1227
01:31:25,029 --> 01:31:27,406
and then go on in the same old way.

1228
01:31:28,700 --> 01:31:33,203
My soul is humble when I see the way
little ones accept their lot.

1229
01:31:34,539 --> 01:31:36,790
Lord save little children.

1230
01:31:36,875 --> 01:31:39,293
The wind blows, and the rains are cold.

1231
01:31:40,336 --> 01:31:43,046
- Yet they abide.
- [ Footsteps Running ]

1232
01:32:02,192 --> 01:32:04,693
[ Watch Ticking ]

1233
01:32:10,700 --> 01:32:13,160
That watch sure is a fine loud ticker.

1234
01:32:14,829 --> 01:32:18,415
Be nice to have someone around the house
who can give me the right time of day.

1235
01:32:19,667 --> 01:32:22,961
This watch
is the nicest watch I ever had.

1236
01:32:23,046 --> 01:32:26,715
Well, a fella just can't go round
with rundown, busted watches.

1237
01:32:33,723 --> 01:32:36,225
They abide, and they endure.


